16:06.066 --> 16:07.900
Ethan: Can I sit?

16:07.935 --> 16:10.236
Barton:
I wouldn't advise it.

16:13.039 --> 16:15.841
Ethan: I don't know what Vivian
has told you about our parting,

16:15.875 --> 16:17.543
- but I want to explain--
- Barton: If I was in the mood

16:17.577 --> 16:21.647
for a postmortem,
I'd go down to the morgue.

16:21.681 --> 16:25.217
Ethan: Sir, your daughter
is smart, she's beautiful,

16:25.252 --> 16:26.619
she knows her own mind--

16:26.653 --> 16:28.453
Barton:
She's devastated, my daughter,

16:28.487 --> 16:31.022
wondering what she did wrong,
how she failed you,

16:31.057 --> 16:33.225
tearing herself up
as if this is her fault

16:33.259 --> 16:34.659
when the truth is,

16:34.693 --> 16:37.295
you're the one that can't find
his own ass with both hands.

16:42.568 --> 16:47.104
Ethan: I'm asking you to
separate your personal feelings

16:47.139 --> 16:49.106
from your professional decision

16:49.141 --> 16:51.409
to terminate me
from this hospital.

16:51.443 --> 16:55.179
Barton: You think I got to be
Provost by holding on to grudges?

16:55.213 --> 16:58.449
I was prepared to accept the
board's decision to hire you,

16:58.484 --> 16:59.817
but I didn't have to.

16:59.851 --> 17:02.386
- You were not recommended.
- Ethan: That can't be true.

17:02.420 --> 17:04.121
I read the letter
Dr. Kernohan wrote.

17:04.156 --> 17:05.222
- It was glowing.
- You failed

17:05.257 --> 17:07.023
your performance review.

17:07.058 --> 17:08.625
Some of your superiors
had concerns

17:08.660 --> 17:12.496
that you lacked the
professionalism and character

17:12.530 --> 17:15.732
to represent this institution.

17:20.570 --> 17:22.306
Ethan: It was Bill.

17:22.339 --> 17:25.040
Barton: I could only vouch for
your lack of character in general.

17:27.944 --> 17:30.980
Ethan: I wanted to love Vivian,
I really did.

17:31.015 --> 17:33.350
But you can't pick
what you love.

17:33.384 --> 17:35.118
Barton:
My daughter dodged a bullet.

17:35.152 --> 17:38.254
Let's leave it at that.

17:38.289 --> 17:41.191
[ Typewriter keys clacking ]

18:07.750 --> 18:09.284
[ Clicks ]

18:31.874 --> 18:33.842
Austin: You know
the heat blast from an H-bomb

18:33.876 --> 18:36.277
can incinerate a telephone pole
2 miles away.

18:36.311 --> 18:39.046
What do you say we get out
of here and take a drive?

18:39.081 --> 18:40.647
Penny: I'm a casualty.

18:40.682 --> 18:42.516
Austin: I'm a doctor.
We're a perfect match.

18:42.550 --> 18:45.086
Penny: Civil defense
is nothing to joke about.

18:45.120 --> 18:48.455
And you should be thinking about
your wife at a time like this.

18:51.426 --> 18:55.429
Austin: Wonder if the secretaries
are friendlier in Moscow.

18:55.463 --> 18:57.498
What?

18:59.834 --> 19:01.234
I don't understand.

19:01.269 --> 19:05.439
Virginia: Honestly,
we're as shocked as you are.

19:05.473 --> 19:08.108
Her name is Flora Banks.

19:09.210 --> 19:11.412
Austin: First of all,
you never told me their names.

19:11.446 --> 19:13.413
